<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{{ lms_content_course_title }}</title>
  <style>
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background: #f0f2f5; color: #222; }
    header { background: #1a3a5c; color: #fff; padding: 20px 40px; }
    header h1 { font-size: 22px; }
    header p  { font-size: 13px; margin-top: 4px; opacity: .8; }
    nav { display: flex; gap: 4px; background: #122a45; padding: 0 40px; }
    nav button { background: none; border: none; color: #adc6e0; padding: 12px 18px;
                 cursor: pointer; font-size: 14px; border-bottom: 3px solid transparent; }
    nav button.active, nav button:hover { color: #fff; border-bottom-color: #4a9fd4; }
    main { max-width: 860px; margin: 30px auto; padding: 0 20px; }
    .tab { display: none; }
    .tab.active { display: block; }
    .card { background: #fff; border-radius: 6px; padding: 28px 32px;
            box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,.1); margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .card h2 { font-size: 18px; color: #1a3a5c; margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .card h3 { font-size: 15px; color: #2c5282; margin: 18px 0 8px; }
    .card p, .card li { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; }
    .card ul, .card ol { padding-left: 22px; margin-top: 6px; }
    .badge { display: inline-block; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 12px;
             font-size: 12px; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .badge.theory { background: #e3f2fd; color: #1565c0; }
    .badge.exercise { background: #fce4ec; color: #b71c1c; }
    .badge.complete { background: #e8f5e9; color: #1b5e20; }
    .highlight { background: #fff8e1; border-left: 4px solid #f9a825;
                 padding: 10px 14px; margin: 12px 0; border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; }
    .checklist label { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 10px;
                       margin-bottom: 10px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 14px; }
    .checklist input { margin-top: 3px; width: 16px; height: 16px; }
    .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 10px 22px; border-radius: 4px;
           border: none; cursor: pointer; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold;
           margin-top: 14px; }
    .btn-primary { background: #1a3a5c; color: #fff; }
    .btn-primary:hover { background: #2c5282; }
    .btn-danger { background: #c0392b; color: #fff; }
    .url-box { background: #f5f5f5; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 4px;
               padding: 8px 12px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px;
               word-break: break-all; margin: 8px 0; }
    .score-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin-top: 12px; }
    .score-item { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 6px; padding: 14px;
                  border-left: 4px solid #4a9fd4; }
    .score-item .weight { font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; color: #1a3a5c; }
    .score-item .label { font-size: 12px; color: #666; margin-top: 2px; }
    footer { text-align: center; padding: 20px; font-size: 12px; color: #888; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>{{ lms_content_course_title }}</h1>
  <p>CyberRangeCZ &mdash; Hands-on Educational Platform &mdash; PUC2-Sub Case 2a</p>
</header>

<nav>
  <button class="active" onclick="showTab('overview', this)">Overview</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('module1', this)">Module 1 &mdash; Sender Analysis</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('module2', this)">Module 2 &mdash; Content Red Flags</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('module3', this)">Module 3 &mdash; Attachments &amp; Reporting</button>
  <button onclick="showTab('exercise', this)">Practical Exercise</button>
</nav>

<main>

<!-- OVERVIEW TAB -->
<div id="overview" class="tab active">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge complete">Course Overview</span>
    <h2>Phishing Attack Awareness Training</h2>
    <p>This self-paced course trains you to identify and respond to phishing attacks.
       Complete all three theory modules before starting the practical exercise.</p>
    <h3>Learning Objectives</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Scrutinise sender information for inconsistencies</li>
      <li>Analyse email content for red flags (grammar errors, urgency, threats)</li>
      <li>Verify attachments and embedded links for legitimacy</li>
      <li>Report suspicious emails using organisational protocols</li>
    </ol>
    <h3>Assessment Scoring</h3>
    <div class="score-grid">
      <div class="score-item"><div class="weight">40%</div><div class="label">Detection accuracy (red flags identified)</div></div>
      <div class="score-item"><div class="weight">30%</div><div class="label">Incident report completeness</div></div>
      <div class="score-item"><div class="weight">20%</div><div class="label">Time to detection and report</div></div>
      <div class="score-item"><div class="weight">+10%</div><div class="label">Bonus: did NOT click the phishing link</div></div>
    </div>
    <h3>Your Lab Inbox</h3>
    <p>Simulated phishing emails will be delivered to your MailHog inbox:</p>
    <div class="url-box">http://mail-relay.internal:8025/</div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="showTab('module1', document.querySelectorAll('nav button')[1])">Start with Module 1 &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- MODULE 1 TAB -->
<div id="module1" class="tab">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge theory">Theory</span>
    <h2>Module 1 &mdash; Scrutinising Sender Information</h2>
    <p>The sender field is the first and most important indicator of a phishing email.
       Attackers use several techniques to make malicious emails appear legitimate.</p>

    <h3>Display Name Spoofing</h3>
    <p>The <em>display name</em> (the friendly name shown in your email client) can be
       set to anything, regardless of the actual email address. Always check the
       <strong>raw email address</strong>, not just the display name.</p>
    <div class="highlight">
      <strong>Example:</strong> "IT Security Team" &lt;attacker@malicious-domain.ru&gt;<br>
      The display name looks legitimate; the domain does not.
    </div>

    <h3>Domain Look-alikes (Typosquatting)</h3>
    <p>Attackers register domains that visually resemble legitimate ones:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>company-security.com</code> vs <code>company.com</code></li>
      <li><code>companysecurity.com</code> (no hyphen)</li>
      <li><code>c0mpany.com</code> (zero instead of letter o)</li>
      <li><code>company.com.attacker.net</code> (legitimate domain as subdomain)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Reply-To Mismatches</h3>
    <p>Even if the <em>From</em> address looks valid, the <em>Reply-To</em> header
       may point to a different domain controlled by the attacker. Always inspect
       email headers.</p>

    <h3>Checklist &mdash; Sender Indicators</h3>
    <div class="checklist">
      <label><input type="checkbox"> The display name matches the actual email address domain</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> The sending domain matches the organisation&rsquo;s known domain</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> No typosquatting (extra characters, wrong TLD, look-alike letters)</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> Reply-To address (if present) matches the From domain</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> Email headers show a valid SPF/DKIM record for the sending domain</label>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="showTab('module2', document.querySelectorAll('nav button')[2])">Next: Module 2 &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- MODULE 2 TAB -->
<div id="module2" class="tab">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge theory">Theory</span>
    <h2>Module 2 &mdash; Analysing Content for Red Flags</h2>
    <p>Even when the sender appears legitimate, the email body often contains
       detectable indicators of a phishing attempt.</p>

    <h3>Urgency and Fear Tactics</h3>
    <p>Phishing emails exploit psychological pressure. Look for language such as:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>"Your account will be <strong>suspended</strong> within 24 hours"</li>
      <li>"<strong>Immediate action required</strong> &mdash; failure to respond will result in&hellip;"</li>
      <li>"<strong>URGENT</strong>: Verify your identity now"</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Legitimate IT systems rarely threaten immediate suspension via email without prior warning.</p>

    <h3>Grammatical and Stylistic Errors</h3>
    <p>While AI-generated phishing has improved, many attacks still contain:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Spelling mistakes and grammatical errors</li>
      <li>Inconsistent capitalisation or punctuation</li>
      <li>Awkward or overly formal phrasing</li>
      <li>Generic salutations ("Dear User", "Dear Customer")</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Suspicious URLs</h3>
    <p>Before clicking any link, hover over it to preview the actual URL. Red flags:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Domain does not match the organisation</li>
      <li>IP address instead of domain name (<code>http://192.168.x.x/login</code>)</li>
      <li>HTTP instead of HTTPS for login pages</li>
      <li>Excessive redirects or URL shorteners (<code>bit.ly</code>, <code>t.co</code>)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Mismatched Branding</h3>
    <p>Logos, colours, and layout that do not match the real organisation&rsquo;s
       branding, or images that fail to load (broken image placeholders).</p>

    <h3>Checklist &mdash; Content Indicators</h3>
    <div class="checklist">
      <label><input type="checkbox"> No artificial urgency or threat language present</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> Salutation uses my correct full name (not "Dear User")</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> No obvious spelling or grammatical errors</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> All hyperlinks point to the expected organisational domain</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> Branding matches the real organisation&rsquo;s style guide</label>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="showTab('module3', document.querySelectorAll('nav button')[3])">Next: Module 3 &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- MODULE 3 TAB -->
<div id="module3" class="tab">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge theory">Theory</span>
    <h2>Module 3 &mdash; Verifying Attachments and Reporting</h2>

    <h3>Attachment Red Flags</h3>
    <p>Malicious attachments are a primary delivery vector. Exercise extreme caution with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Executable files:</strong> <code>.exe</code>, <code>.bat</code>, <code>.ps1</code>, <code>.vbs</code>, <code>.js</code></li>
      <li><strong>Office macro documents:</strong> <code>.docm</code>, <code>.xlsm</code> (macros disabled by default for a reason)</li>
      <li><strong>Archive files:</strong> <code>.zip</code>, <code>.rar</code>, <code>.7z</code> (may conceal malicious payloads)</li>
      <li><strong>PDF files:</strong> can contain embedded JavaScript or exploit links</li>
      <li><strong>Double extensions:</strong> <code>invoice.pdf.exe</code> (the real extension is <code>.exe</code>)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Safe Verification Steps</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Do <strong>not</strong> open the attachment on your workstation</li>
      <li>Check the file extension carefully (enable "show file extensions" in Windows)</li>
      <li>Verify with the sender via a <strong>separate channel</strong> (phone, Teams) &mdash; not by replying to the email</li>
      <li>Submit the file to IT Security for sandbox analysis if in doubt</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Reporting Protocols</h3>
    <p>Reporting a suspicious email quickly is as important as detecting it. Your options:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>GoPhish Report Button:</strong> If the email was sent via GoPhish, use the "Report Phishing" button in the email client or landing page &mdash; this records your detection in the training platform.</li>
      <li><strong>REP Incident Form:</strong> Submit a detection report via the REP Practical Labs incident form, documenting all identified indicators.</li>
      <li><strong>IT Security Helpdesk:</strong> Forward the suspicious email as an attachment to <code>security@company.internal</code> (in a real scenario).</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="highlight">
      <strong>Key principle:</strong> When in doubt, do NOT click. Report first, investigate later with IT Security support.
    </div>

    <h3>Checklist &mdash; Attachment and Reporting</h3>
    <div class="checklist">
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have NOT opened any suspicious attachments</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I verified the attachment type and extension are expected</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I confirmed the request through a separate communication channel</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox"> I have submitted a report documenting all identified red flags</label>
    </div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="showTab('exercise', document.querySelectorAll('nav button')[4])">Start Practical Exercise &rarr;</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- EXERCISE TAB -->
<div id="exercise" class="tab">
  <div class="card">
    <span class="badge exercise">Practical Exercise</span>
    <h2>Phishing Detection Exercise</h2>
    <p>You are now ready to begin the practical exercise. A simulated phishing email
       has been (or will be) delivered to your lab inbox.</p>

    <h3>Step 1 &mdash; Check Your Lab Inbox</h3>
    <p>Open the MailHog WebUI to view your simulated inbox:</p>
    <div class="url-box">http://mail-relay.internal:8025/</div>

    <h3>Step 2 &mdash; Analyse the Email</h3>
    <p>Using the checklists from Modules 1&ndash;3, inspect the email and identify
       as many phishing indicators as possible. Do <strong>NOT</strong> click any
       links unless you are deliberately testing detection (clicking the phishing
       link will be recorded).</p>

    <h3>Step 3 &mdash; Submit Your Detection Report</h3>
    <p>Document your findings in the incident report form below and submit it.
       Include every red flag you identified.</p>

    <form id="reportForm" onsubmit="submitReport(event)" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:12px;">
        <label style="font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;">Your name / trainee ID</label><br>
        <input type="text" id="trainee" required style="width:100%;padding:8px;margin-top:4px;border:1px solid #ccc;border-radius:4px;">
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom:12px;">
        <label style="font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;">Is this email suspicious? *</label><br>
        <label style="font-size:14px;"><input type="radio" name="verdict" value="yes" required> Yes &mdash; this is a phishing attempt</label><br>
        <label style="font-size:14px;"><input type="radio" name="verdict" value="no"> No &mdash; this email appears legitimate</label>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom:12px;">
        <label style="font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;">Red flags identified (one per line) *</label><br>
        <textarea id="indicators" required rows="6" style="width:100%;padding:8px;margin-top:4px;border:1px solid #ccc;border-radius:4px;font-size:13px;" placeholder="Example:&#10;- Sender domain does not match company domain&#10;- Urgent language: 'account suspended in 24h'&#10;- Link points to phishing-simulator.internal, not company domain&#10;- Generic salutation 'Dear [FirstName]'"></textarea>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-bottom:12px;">
        <label style="font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;">Did you click the link in the email?</label><br>
        <label style="font-size:14px;"><input type="radio" name="clicked" value="no"> No &mdash; I did not click the link</label><br>
        <label style="font-size:14px;"><input type="radio" name="clicked" value="yes"> Yes &mdash; I clicked the link (note: this is recorded)</label>
      </div>
      <button type="submit" class="btn btn-danger">Submit Detection Report</button>
    </form>
    <div id="reportResult" style="display:none;" class="highlight" style="margin-top:16px;"></div>
  </div>
</div>

</main>

<footer>
  CyberRangeCZ &mdash; PUC2-Sub Case 2a &mdash; Hands-on Educational Platform &mdash;
  Reporting Workspace: <a href="http://reporting.internal:3000/" style="color:#4a9fd4;">http://reporting.internal:3000/</a>
</footer>

<script>
function showTab(id, btn) {
  document.querySelectorAll('.tab').forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
  document.querySelectorAll('nav button').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
  document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');
  btn.classList.add('active');
}

function submitReport(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  var trainee   = document.getElementById('trainee').value;
  var indicators = document.getElementById('indicators').value;
  var verdict   = document.querySelector('input[name="verdict"]:checked');
  var clicked   = document.querySelector('input[name="clicked"]:checked');

  var result = document.getElementById('reportResult');
  result.style.display = 'block';
  result.innerHTML =
    '<strong>Report submitted.</strong><br>' +
    'Trainee: ' + trainee + '<br>' +
    'Verdict: ' + (verdict ? verdict.value : 'not selected') + '<br>' +
    'Link clicked: ' + (clicked ? clicked.value : 'not answered') + '<br>' +
    'Indicators documented: ' + indicators.split('\n').filter(l => l.trim()).length + '<br><br>' +
    'Your instructor will review results in the Grafana Reporting Workspace.<br>' +
    '<a href="http://reporting.internal:3000/">View Cohort Dashboard &rarr;</a>';
}
</script>

</body>
</html>
